ebb /ɛb/

(ebbing,ebbed,ebbs) 

1. V-I When the tide or the sea ebbs , its level gradually falls. 退潮 

例： When the tide ebbs, you can paddle out for a mile and barely get your ankles wet. 退潮时，你可以蹚水走出1英里远而几乎湿不到脚踝。 

2. N-COUNT The ebb or the ebb tide is one of the regular periods, usually two per day, when the sea gradually falls to a lower level as the tide moves away from the land. 退潮 

例： ...the spring ebb tide. …春季的退潮。 

3. V-I If someone's life, support, or feeling ebbs , it becomes weaker and gradually disappears. 衰退 [正式] 

例： Were there occasions when enthusiasm ebbed? 热情会有衰退的时候吗？ 

4. PHRASAL VERB Ebb away means the same as . 衰退 

例： His little girl's life ebbed away. 他小女儿的生命衰竭了。 

5. PHRASE If someone or something is at a low ebb or at their lowest ebb , they are not very successful or profitable. 处于低潮 

例： ...a time when everyone is tired and at a low ebb. …一个每人都处于疲惫状态和低潮的时刻

